title: BNP Asadullah Baloch wins PB-29 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Balochistan National Party (BNP) candidate Mir Asadullah Baloch has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-29, Panjgur-I by securing 7,263 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was National Party (NP) candidate Muhammad Aslam Baloch who bagged 4,547 votes.
Overall voters turnout remained 28.73 per cent.
